      "title": "100 Greek and Roman Mythology Writing Prompts - EveryWriter",
      "url": "https://www.everywritersresource.com/100-greek-and-roman-mythology-writing-prompts/",
      "content": "Write a short story about a demigod child of Ares who is a pacifist struggling with family expectations he or she doesn’t agree with. Retell the story of Narcissus staring at himself eternally in the waters of a pool from Narcissus’s best friend who desperately misses who he used to be. Imagine you are Bellerophon, the legendary Greek hero who tamed the winged horse Pegasus."
    },
    {
      "title": "What are some good Greek mythology writing prompts? - Quora",
      "url": "https://www.quora.com/What-are-some-good-Greek-mythology-writing-prompts",
      "content": "Answer (1 of 3): Apollo had had enough. It’s payback time! As Artemis crept through the forest, she heard a branch snap close behind her. Zeus grabbed the remote, eager to see what was going on in the world. Hades saw the portent and it was not good. Medusa was having a bad hair day again. T..."
    },
